               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p>The <title xml:lang="ta">Villipāratam</title>.</p>
<p>This appears to be an old manuscript, with several damaged leaves, supplemented by later hands. For instance:
  <list>
    <item>U2 and U4, each made of a single folio, have almost the same text, but by two different hands. U4 appears as a replacement copy for U2.</item>
    <item>U3 is a single folio, much damaged, which has exactly the same text as U5, f1, which appears to be a replacement copy of U3.</item>
    <item>U5, f201<hi rend="superscript">2</hi>, is an addition, unblackened, by another hand, inserted in the old manuscript.</item>
    </list>
</p>
<p>Description based on the digital images available on Gallica.</p></summary>
                  
